Questions:
Which of the following is considered the experimental therapy being tested in this study for patients with brain cancer?
A) Regular neuropsychological evaluations and recommendations from Dr. Loughan;
B) The Managing Cancer and Living Meaningfully (CALM) intervention program;
C) Standard medical care for brain metastasis at the VCU Massey Cancer Center;
D) Access to usual care in clinic for any mental health or cognitive concerns.

Correct answer: B) The Managing Cancer and Living Meaningfully (CALM) intervention program.

If you choose not to participate in the CALM intervention study, what standard care options are available to you for managing mental health or cognitive concerns related to your diagnosis and treatment?
A) You will be provided with a list of community resources for mental health support; 
B) You will receive regular neuropsychological evaluations and recommendations from Dr. Loughan; 
C) You will be enrolled in an alternative research study focusing on physical rehabilitation; 
D) You will be given access to a series of self-help books on managing distress in cancer patients.

Correct answer: B

If you have questions about your rights as a participant in the Managing Distress in Malignant Brain Cancer study, or if you wish to discuss any problems or concerns, whom should you contact?

A) The Department of Defense;
B) The Principal Investigator, Dr. Ashlee Loughan;
C) Virginia Commonwealth University Office of Research;
D) Your personal physician.

Correct answer: C) Virginia Commonwealth University Office of Research.
